# First we need to check the reference agent who is initiating the request and need to check whether that person is also registered as a customer care role, then only the self-assignment process will work. -{color:#0747a6} *Why do we need to check the reference agent who is initiating the request?*{color}{color:#0747a6} {color}{color:#0747a6}*I see only one check is needed here. If the logged-in user is customer care, then start the self-assignment process. Kindly* {color}

* As you can see this reference agent is *inactive* then also it is allowing to login as reference agent account. So we need to check this status and perform the operations against this status. - {color:#0747a6}*Again, no need, if the logged-in user is customer care, then start the self-assignment process*{color}
* So we need to maintain another status or need to verify this status, where it is used and here user *has multi role* which we need to check as well. - {color:#0747a6}*No, we only care that the logged-in user IS of type customer care,..* {color}
* Here there is a mechanism of self-assignment which was not there in previous CR. - {color:#0747a6}*This is where the CR starts* {color}
* Also in the initiate request list, need to display the dropdown if the user is a reference agent. - {color:#0747a6}*Is this in relation to*{color} [https://solvit-app.atlassian.net/browse/SR-950|https://solvit-app.atlassian.net/browse/SR-950|smart-link]{color:#0747a6}*, if yes, the hours for this should not be counted in this CR as then they will be duplicated.*{color}

